               <p>JOHN COLES. I am a <rs id="t18270712-74-viclabel410" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-74-victim495 t18270712-74-viclabel410"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270712-74-crimeloc411">Princes-street, Lisson-grove</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-74-crimeloc411" type="placeName" value="Princes-street, Lisson-grove"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-74-crimeloc411" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-74-off408 t18270712-74-crimeloc411"></join>. On the 9th of June, between twelve and one o'clock. I saw the prisoner take a deal from a<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182707120040"></xptr>pile which had not been sawed an hour before; my men were gone to dinner - he was quite a stranger. I was standing in the street, and saw him come and take up the deal, and mark it TB - he carried it about twelve yards from my premises. I went to him, and he said some man had told him he might have it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was out of work, and a person came and told me to carry this up to the Yorkshire Stingo, and he would give me 6d.</p>
